public class StatementTable
extends ExternalType

StatementTable holds the statement values. This class manages the statements through the #addStatement(TableStatement, int) operation.

1.3 Derives from ExternalType

addStatement

public int addStatement(StatementTable.TableStatement tblStatement,
                        Statement statement,
                        int did)
Adds a statement to the statements set. The insertion index and statement occurrences are also indexed in the index and count map.

Uses statement ids as 1-based to support nested statements as an int.

Parameters:
tblStatement - StatementTable.TableStatement, the statement to be added to the statements set
did - Document index
Returns:
int, the index of the added statement, which is 'int' datatype since it cannot be null
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if statement is null

_from

protected void _from(ObjectInput in,
                     ReadCache cache)
              throws IOException
Reads itself from the input. The supplied cache is an ancillary structure allowing the implementing type to reference a cached copy of an object by its hash value.

The use of the cache is not required. However the use or disuse of the cache should be symmetric according to both ExternalType._from(ObjectInput, ReadCache) and ExternalType._to(ObjectOutput, WriteCache). Put differently, the cache use should be identical in both methods.
